{
  "texts": [
    "Selective regularization on high-reward tokens yields better results.",
    "As shown in Eq. 1, T-REG can be interpreted as performing weighted SFT on high-reward tokens.",
    "Previous methods (Dubey et al., 2024; Xu et al., 2024) apply an SFT loss over the entire preferred output y w, which has been shown to help prevent degeneration: However, as shown in Table 2, incorporating this loss results in significant performance degradation on both tasks, even with a small α value.",
    "This is likely because optimizing over the entire y w includes tokens of lower quality.",
    "In contrast, T-REG -focuses exclusively on high-reward tokensachieves consistent improvements over DPO."
  ]
}